@group
    @title=Namespace Gehtsoft.Tools.Log
    @key=Gehtsoft.Tools.Log
    @ingroup=index
    @brief=The common logging interface.

    The main point of the this log interface is that the process of detection whether the log level is on is perfectly simplified and allows
    you to avoid needless formatting and calls in case the log level is off.

    The following pattern is used:

    [c]myLogService.Debug?.Log("logMessage");[/c]

    This namespace and assembly defines interfaces only.

    You can use various implementations of this log interface or provide your own.

    The following implementations are readily available:

    [clink=Gehtsoft.Tools.Log.RollingFile]Gehtsoft.Tools.Log.RollingFile[/clink] for simple and lightweight rolling file log implementation.

    [clink=Gehtsoft.Tools.Log.Serilog]Gehtsoft.Tools.Log.Serilog[/clink] for wrapper over [eurl=https://serilog.net/]Serilog[/eurl] log library.
@end
